refine /rɪˈfaɪn/

(refining,refined,refines) 

1. V-T When a substance is refined , it is made pure by having all other substances removed from it. 提炼 [usu passive] 

例： Oil is refined to remove naturally occurring impurities. 油经过提炼去除天然生成的杂质。 

2. refining N-UNCOUNT 提炼 

例： ...oil refining. …炼油。 

3. V-T If something such as a process, theory, or machine is refined , it is improved by having small changes made to it. 完善 [usu passive] 

例： Surgical techniques are constantly being refined. 外科手术技术正在不断得到完善。

